content: Quick, light, and straightforward app for AD tasks on the go. Been using it for years; would love to see an update, but no real need.
Good little app, works well
Still the best around. Would pay again to have the gui updated to look nicer. But can't complain. Would like to add a feature when you open the app to trigger a VPN.
Love this app.  Does what I need!
I love this app. I do wish it was modernized a little.
Work fine, user interface can be improved
Works very well, only thing missing is option to add new AD user. I hope this feature gets added in a future release soon.
Please tell us how to use after configuration show message can't server
The app just doesn't work, it won't connect to my server 2008 r2 ad... tried every connection option with no luck

After the latest Android update it no longer works.  The app was last updated in 2013.  I don't think the author supports it anymore as the link to email for assistance from the developer is no longer working.
So far no issues.  BUT can't add users, can't create groups etc. Id maybe expect that in the free version, but not there paid.
The app does not work and is a waste of money
Works pretty well.  A little bit of trouble with screen display when scrolling.  I'd have given it 4 stars if I could add users too.
Really really useful tool.

This was a great app for me and I used it all the time. That is until my phone upgrade to marshmallow yesterday. No matter what I do I can't get it to connect to my domain anymore. Weather I connect to VPN or locally as soon as I click the domain I want it says cannot connect to server. I have a Droid Turbo 2 at this upgrade the marshmallow yesterday. I hope this is fixed soon especially since I had to pay for this app
How do I install this on both my androids?

You can move a computer if you first find it in the tree, but not from the full list of computers. Also, from the computer list you can't discover what OU a computer is in. The same is true for users. So the actions you may perform vary depending on how you're accessing the objects. That's ridiculous. You should be able to do whatever you can do in the application, from wherever you can tap & hold to get the menu. Why artificially limit actions the app can perform, out of careless inconsistency?
Used to be a great app. Now when you select a user it crashes out. Reports to developer are ignored.
Pretty decent for basic AD administration. Loses a point for the horrible interface and another for the LDAP search base not being implemented. Otherwise does a reasonable job.
Well, thanks to goole play survey.. anyway, this is about this app. Good, works and handy.. but one suggestion though  put "Find expired account"  Update:

This is a very useful app for on the go AD admin. I would like it more if the search feature worked and if I could delete accounts instead of just disable them. Otherwise, I've been using it for three years and it makes my life easier.  Well worth the money.
Very handy for doing mundane AD tasks on the run.
Would be nice to have a material upgrade, but it works great on a functionality level
Works wonders, solid no issues.

I often use it when I'm at work or remotely (through VPN). It saved me from booting my computer more than once. I'm not sure the app is still maintained, but it would benefit from a little interface update, and with ARC Welder this would be great to be able to run this app from any Chrome-powered systems (Chromebook for example).
use this all the time with junos pulse, resetting passwords on the go is a snap with this app
This is a great app to manage exisitig users but there is no way to add OUs, containers, or even new users. I hope future updates will include these options.
Will not connect on HTC one m8.  Using the same configuration as on my HTC one m7.  Please fix
Works great!  Full access to users, groups and devices.
App works great and is very useful but please refresh the GUI. Would be perfect if it looked even remotely modern
Very helpful to see all locked accounts in one easy step.
Great access to AD without logging into the server directly! Get some!
Finally can manage AD without running back to the office to the desktop.
Able to edit and keep up with users on the fly

I want to start off by saying that this app works great and has been incredibly useful. That being said, it could use a bit of a makeover, namely, current design guidelines and larger tap targets for things like usernames and computers. Thanks!
On a note 3, constantly if left open new the background will crash when you reopen it.   In search field, pressing return gives a line break instead of searching. REALLY? makes me miss iOS.
...the GUI.
I have the pro version and I use it every day.  It is very easy to use on that 3 AM lockout or AD problem.  Very nice.  Prefer to mmc for ease if use!
The free version worked right away so I bought this version. So useful...would be great if the GUI was updated...
Like a handheld remote to a DC x
Comes in handy a lot on the run.
Very useful for moving computers from one OU to another on the fly! Well worth the money!
This app works great, but man is it ugly. This can also cause issues with hitting the spots you want due to the targets being too small.   I'd pay money for a version with a UI overhaul.
This thing is a life saver and so handy. Works really well ! Thank you developer of this app

Paired with a VPN client this app allows basic view & edit capabilities in active directory.  I wouldn't want to try much more than account unlocks and password resets, but it handles those actions well and has a handy feature to let you get straight to locked accounts.  A few pounds to avoid having to find a computer to do a password reset seems fair to me.
It would be 5 stars if I could edit extended fields. I'd also like to see password changes without SSL/TLS.
Brilliant Tool. Works well on Note 1 so I don't have to carry around a laptop or tablet.
Finally setup TLS on windows 2003 server and this saves me so much time when walking through the building. Having over 200 users doesn't make resetting passwords easy. Thanks this app works great!

The user search function just doesn't work. I like this app cause I can browse AD through the tree just fine. I can remote to computers with the junction-ed RDP app. I can unlock and lock loaned laptops. I can go to an office and reset a users password for them, BUT only if I can find them. If they are a new hire, there is no guarantee that they were placed in the correct AD container. So I have to go back to my desk and find them. This isn't too much of a hassle for new employees. But, when I'm helping a classroom of 100 new students, most of whom can't log in because they didn't read their email, it becomes a problem.
Great for managing users while on the go.
Does just what it should and provides much needed functionality. A must have for any domain admin.
Perfect AD management a must have
Should remove the save password option for security reasons. Would deploy to my techies if this was not removed.
Outstanding product works great with Nexus 7. Would like more features but man it is sold and worth the money.

This is going to be my goto when I'm too lazy to pull out my laptop!  For simply actions like reset password, disable users, moving objects or even changing memberships & details this is exactly what I've been looking for.

I use this at work. Overall, I love it. I don't need to carry my laptop with me anymore when making simple AD changes, which is really nice. There could be an option to change appearance, such as resizing the text.

Works pretty good but by no means is this a tool that could be just used instead of the AD MMC console.  If your on the road and in a small AD jam then most likely this app can get it done for you.  The UI needs a lot of work.  It just not very intuitive.  It's pretty sloppy.  If the developer were to add create user and a better UI I would give it 5 stars.
Most useful app after taking
Must have administration tool

This is a useful app for when I am on the road to be able to perform simple AD Tasks. But the one feature which is mosy noticible by its absence, is the New User.  Whilst on client sites I often need to create a new user account to give them access to our help desk, as it stands, I must use my laptop to perform this task, life wold be so much better if I could do this with my Android.  I noticed it is on your RoadMap, I was just wondering when it might be implemented?
Works well so far, but DO NOT save your password in the connection profile. This app stores it in plain text if you do!
Awesome. I can reset passwords etc from no matter where I am at in the office. If I am out of the office. I simply connect to VPN on phone and  run app. Love it.
Wonderful start to what will surely become a powerhouse app! Keep up the good work and updates!
Great for quick fixes or checkups on multiple ADs.
It would be 5 if it could add computer objects.  Thx
This works just as advertised!!!
Awesome app. Worth every cent paid.

I love this app but feel there is still room for some extra features. Features such be able to mange a PC ie add user permission like you can from AD. That feature alone would really make this tool priceless.

One of a kind application on Android.  It's similar to AD Helpdesk for iOS. It saves me at least an hour per day with password resets/unlockes. I cannot wait for the tablet mode. Fast and thorough support from the developer. Keep up the good work Andy Beal !
If you have Android and run an AD environment then you HAVE to get this app. Add the rdp client and you have a superb way to mange your domain.
Great app. Makes life easier when im on standby and have to help users out. Can unlock users and reset password when away from my pc. Must have on GS2
This is a totally professional application for AD administration! Everything works perfectly! You have to use this if you work with AD!
I have been using it for the past 3 months and it works flawlessly. If you are a domain admin you need this!
Works amazingly well. Very well designed with great features for AD management.
This program does what is says it will do. It resets Active directory user passwords flawlessly! It works great on my Archos 101 Internet tablet!
Can't seem to reset user passwords after update. Only reason i got app
Overall your app is good only issue I find is that, it should be able to let the user choose what vnc or rdp and not just the ones you want us to use.
IT WORKS! I have been looking for an app like this since I got my phone.
